Senate Resolution 80
By: Senators Burns of the 23rd, Hickman of the 4th and Anderson of the 24th
A RESOLUTION
1 Commending Robert Michael "Mike" Kile; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, Robert Michael "Mike" Kile began his distinguished law enforcement career
3 in 1969 as a patrolman with the Sardis Police Department in Burke County, Georgia, and the
4 following year he became a deputy sheriff in Screven County; and
5 WHEREAS, he was appointed chief deputy under Sheriff George Bazemore before being
6 named chief of police in Hiltonia, Georgia, in 1984, where he served for eight years; and
7 WHEREAS, in 1992, he was elected sheriff of Screven County, assuming office on January
8 1, 1993, and serving as the county's chief officer for 32 years, during which time he oversaw
9 the planning and construction of a 175-bed facility designed to replace the county's aging
10 1930s jail; and
11 WHEREAS, over his 55 year-long career, he has demonstrated unwavering dedication to his
12 country and community, ensuring the safety of Screven County's residents, including his wife
13 of 50 years, Helen, as well as their three daughters, four grandchildren, and one
14 great-grandchild; and
