15 WHEREAS, he is an honest and dedicated public servant who strives for excellence in all
16 of his endeavors and whose primary concern is the welfare and safety of the citizens of
17 Screven County; and
18 WHEREAS, he is highly regarded by the citizens of his community and by state and local
19 government officials as a man of unquestioned integrity and dedication to the administration
20 of justice and sound principles of law enforcement; and
21 WHEREAS, this spirited law enforcement professional has exhibited extraordinary devotion
22 to duty, outstanding loyalty, fine leadership, and meticulous attention to detail in all of his
23 duties; and
24 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that gratitude is expressed for the unique and
25 often unheralded contributions of local law enforcement professionals on behalf of the
26 citizens of this state.
27 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that the members of this body
28 commend the care, courage, sympathy, and selfless dedication exhibited by Robert Michael
29 "Mike" Kile in carrying out the difficult duties of his vocation and express their utmost
30 appreciation for having so purely and truly defined for others the meaning of public servant.
31 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Secretary of the Senate is authorized and directed
32 to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to Robert Michael
33 "Mike" Kile.
